## Pages naming and tab structure

These rules apply to `src/pages/**`. In Core Directories above, the `pages/` entry references this section for details.

### Page naming

- Entity view (details): `{entity}-details`
- Entity list: `{entity}-list`
- Entity create/update: `{entity}-create` / `{entity}-update`
- Non-entity pages (abstract areas like settings, login): plain names without postfixes (`settings`, `login`, etc.)

Examples:

```
src/pages/
  {entity}-details/
  {entity}-list/
  {entity}-create/
  settings/
  login/
```

### Tabs in app vs. pages content

- Tabs are defined at the routing level in `app/**` (e.g., dynamic routes like `app/(authenticated)/entities/[slug]/tab/page.tsx`).
- Each tab re-exports a page component that lives under `src/pages/**` in a directory named for that tab's content/domain.
- This allows `app` to handle navigation and layout, while `src/pages` holds the tab content and business logic.

Example (neutral):

```
app/(authenticated)/entities/[slug]/ (default tab redirect is set in next.config.ts)
  layout.tsx           // Entity layout (sidebar/header)
  overview/page.tsx    // Re-export from pages/overview
  items/page.tsx       // Re-export from pages/item-list
  settings/page.tsx    // Re-export from pages/settings (abstract)

src/pages/
  overview/
    ui/
      Overview.tsx
    index.ts
  item-list/
    ui/
      ItemList.tsx
    index.ts
  settings/
    ui/
      Settings.tsx
    index.ts
```

### Tabs within a single entity-details page

When all tabs belong to the same entity (e.g., multiple views of one `{entity}`), place tabs as components inside `{entity}-details/ui/` and compose them in `EntityDetails.tsx`.

Example:

```
{entity}-details/
  ui/
    EntityDetails.tsx
    EntityInfoTab.tsx
    EntityConfigTab.tsx
    index.ts
```

### Tabs within abstract areas (non-entity pages)

For abstract areas like settings, login, or other non-entity pages that have multiple tabs, structure them as separate components within the abstract area's `ui/` folder.

Example:

```
settings/
  ui/
    SettingsGeneral.tsx
    SettingsSecurity.tsx
    SettingsPayment.tsx
    index.ts
  index.ts
```

Guidelines:

- Keep tabs focused and independent; pass only required props.
- In `app/**`, re-export components from `src/pages/**` for each tab route.
- Re-export public components from `ui/index.ts` for clean imports.
- For abstract areas, use the pattern `{Area}{TabName}.tsx` (e.g., `SettingsGeneral.tsx`).
